
Archive files are files that contain a set of files.
-
Such an archive file is used for at least three purposes:
  • Distributing files
  • Backing up (archiving) files (hence the name)
  • Save disk space (→ Linux/shell/commands/tar[`tar`] files in combination with → Linux/shell/commands/gzip[`gzip`]).

sa:
   → Linux/shell/commands/zip[`zip`]
